name: NewbornAffectedByUmbilicalCordComplicationsS
title: Newborn Affected by Umbilical Cord Complications S
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains diagnoses most commonly used for newborns with umbilical cord complications.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify newborns who have an active  diagnosis of umbilical cord complications. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Diagnosis" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing the SNOMED-CT code system for the diagnosis of umbilical cord complications including umbilical thrombosis and vaso previa.),(Exclusion Criteria: None.)
